---
// Figma file u4NLOVKuXUTKULhSn0sAJQ: CTA group 1:16266 (y2978.28-3254.11).
// H2 1:16268 "Found your entry point?" (real text node, reports
// Faculty_Glyphic:Regular, 65px, fill #1e1e3c — genuine serifs confirmed on a
// direct screenshot, so no "wrapping-group misreports Faculty" correction is
// needed here, unlike the eyebrows elsewhere on this page/Home).
// Paragraph 1:16269 (outlined, no text node — ~180 glyph-outline vectors,
// 2 lines). Pill group 1:16367 ("Register your interest": 1:16368 pill body,
// 1:16370/1:16373 arrow circle + glyph, 1:16374/1:16377 label glyph group
// 1:16378-1:16397) — screenshot-confirmed as the same navy-pill/orange-circle/
// navy-arrow "filled" treatment already built into PillButton.astro (no
// variant fork needed).
//
// SectionHeading-vs-own-markup decision (required by this task's brief): NO
// eyebrow sibling exists anywhere near this heading. Verified exhaustively —
// get_metadata swept every node with y in [2840, 3400] (the full span from
// Programs' O-card row bottom to the Footer chrome's own top, 1:17186 at
// y3394): 128 nodes total, every single one accounted for as either the H2
// text, one of the paragraph's glyph-outline vectors, or one of the pill's
// own fill/circle/arrow/label paths. No text node, no vector group, nothing
// eyebrow-shaped. So this section uses its own markup rather than
// SectionHeading (whose contract is eyebrow+H2) — the same call Hero.astro
// made for its H1 (see that file's own frontmatter for the parallel
// reasoning) and exactly Home's CtaBand precedent (also eyebrow-less).
//
// Decoration inventory (house rule: every visible design element is in
// scope, per the plan's Global Constraints): the SAME exhaustive y[2840,3400]
// sweep found ZERO sparks/curves/chevrons/decorative vectors in or around
// this section — confirmed against the screenshot too (flat cream
// background, no ornament). Unlike its siblings (Hero's orbital curves +
// sparks, HowItWorks'/Programs' chevrons + flourish), this section is
// genuinely bare, matching Home's CtaBand (also zero decoration) rather than
// the plan preamble's "sibling sections here have sparks/curves" caveat —
// that line describes the page overall, not every section on it.
//
// Glyph-verify (brief requirement): a 6x-zoomed render of the paragraph node
// shows a plain straight apostrophe in "you're" (a simple vertical stroke,
// not the angled teardrop of a curly '), unlike Hero.astro's "India's" (node
// 1:16971, curly &rsquo;, verified independently in Task 2) — kept literal
// here rather than normalized to the house's more common curly form,
// per the standing verify-per-node-not-per-house-pattern principle already
// established across this page (see e.g. Hero.astro's .lede fill-color
// comment). "MC²+" glyph-verified as a true superscript 2 (matches Hero's
// MC&sup2;+ treatment) via the same zoomed render.
import PillButton from "../PillButton.astro";
---

<section class="cta-band">
  <div class="container heading">
    <h2>Found your entry point?</h2>
    <p class="body">
      The first MC&sup2;+ cohort launches in August 2026. Applications open
      soon. Tell us what you're building in the meantime.
    </p>
    <div class="cta">
      <!-- No dedicated "apply"/"register" route exists anywhere in the
           site's nav/route map (see src/data/nav.ts) for this CTA — /contact
           is the user's standing catch-all destination for CTAs without a
           home of their own. -->
      <PillButton label="Register your interest" href="/contact" />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .cta-band {
    background: var(--color-cream);
    /* Gap from Programs' own card row bottom (all four O-cards share height
       606.86px on a shared top y2239.91, per Programs.astro's own comment —
       bottom 2846.77) to this H2's own top (1:16268, y2978.28) is 131.51px.
       Programs.astro already contributes 6rem/96px of that via its own
       padding-bottom (untouched — out of this task's file scope), leaving
       131.51 - 96 = 35.51px (2.2194rem) as this section's own share — same
       "subtract the already-built neighbor's contribution" technique as
       Home's CtaBand top-padding derivation. */
    padding-top: 2.2194rem;
    /* Gap from this section's own bottom (the pill, 1:16367, bottom
       y3254.11) to the Footer chrome's own top (1:17186, y3394 exactly) is
       139.89px (8.7431rem). Footer is chrome/untouched, so — per Home's
       CtaBand precedent, which attributed its own equivalent gap entirely to
       itself rather than splitting it with Footer's internal top padding —
       this section's padding-bottom carries the full measured gap. */
    padding-bottom: 8.7431rem;
  }

  .heading {
    text-align: center;
  }

  h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 4.0625rem; /* 65px, node 1:16268 (real text node, direct report) */
    line-height: 1.07; /* site-wide constant for this exact Faculty-65px H2 role (Pillars/Audiences/Home's CtaBand baseline-derived; this H2 is single-line so can't be independently re-derived, reusing the confirmed constant rather than guessing) */
    color: var(--color-ink-alt); /* #1e1e3c exact match */
  }

  .body {
    /* 9.97px, gap between the H2's own bbox bottom (1:16268, ends y3062.28)
       and the paragraph group's bbox top (1:16269, starts y3072.25). */
    margin: 0.6231rem auto 0;
    /* 749.9999px, node 1:16269's own bbox width — matches its parent group
       1:16267's width exactly, confirming (like Home's CtaBand paragraph)
       that this outlined paragraph's own longest wrapped line is the widest
       element in the group. */
    max-width: 46.875rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    /* Outlined vectors, no text node (node 1:16269's ~180 child paths) —
       same situation as Home's CtaBand .body. font-size reused from that
       exact sibling (1.4375rem/23px, itself empirically verified there as
       the smallest size reproducing its design's own line-break points) as
       a starting point, then independently re-verified here in a real
       browser at THIS paragraph's own text and 46.875rem column: it
       reproduces this design's own confirmed 2-line break ("...Applications"
       / "open soon...") exactly, so no further adjustment was needed. */
    font-size: 1.4375rem;
    line-height: 1.4; /* reused from Home's CtaBand .body — same outlined-Sora-body-copy role */
    color: var(--color-gray);
  }

  .cta {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    /* 47.41px, gap between the paragraph group's bbox bottom (1:16269, ends
       y3130.70) and the pill's own top (1:16367, starts y3178.11). */
    margin-top: 2.9631rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1023.98px) {
    h2 {
      font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 6vw, 4.0625rem);
    }
    .body {
      max-width: 90%;
    }
  }
</style>
